content.description: At the top of 'Easy Lieback' head to the right side of the obvious fin at the top of the cliff. Climb through a steep groove, then hand traverse the fin left, sling the fin's tip and make a difficult mantle to the top.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description: This route starts 30 feet to the right of “Decent Exposure’. Climb up the dihedral, left-facing arete past an overhang system and several smaller overhangs to the rappel tree.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description: Same start as ‘Easy Lieback’. From the tree climb up a groove to a roof. Pass over the roof and into the dihedral above it. Climb right and into a small chimney then up several cracks to the upper roof and then to the top.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

climbs.name: Easy Lieback
climbs.fa: 1950 Nicholas Clifford, Tim Mutch & PMC Members

content.description: Scramble up to the start ledge just below the large, left-facing arete at a tree. Starting 10 feet left of the tree, climb the blank slab up. Continue up and over an overhang joining with the main arete again 75 feet off the ledge. At the top of the arete work your way left to the ledge. From the left-side of the ledges climb up and left to the top.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description:
Same start as ‘Easy Lieback’. 

Pitch 1: Climb up from the tree to the right on the ledges just right of the arete. Climb up and right of the arete about 60 feet to a prow and white face. Climb left into a dihedral above another face and up to a ledge. Belay here. 

Pitch 2: Traverse right 35 to 45 feet to a rappel tree.
content.protection: Standard gap rack: Small to medium cams, 2 large cams, set of stoppers, few small tri-cams.

content.description: This wall starts about 150 to 170 feet right of ‘Warpath Wall’. On the right side of this wall is a large, left-facing arete. These left-facing aretes area common feature is this glacier carved region. All of the routes in this section begin 30 feet up on a ledge.
